WEBVTT

00:00:11.011 --> 00:00:14.973
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:00:41.416 --> 00:00:44.836
<i>Things suddenly took a strange turn after he got a call.</i>

00:01:42.435 --> 00:01:43.436
Se-yun?

00:01:45.647 --> 00:01:47.231
Se-yun!

00:01:47.232 --> 00:01:49.108
<i>And it turned into a chase.</i>

00:01:49.109 --> 00:01:50.235
Hey, stop!

00:02:04.415 --> 00:02:05.625
Mrs. Ahn?

00:02:07.377 --> 00:02:08.253
What are you...

00:02:17.345 --> 00:02:18.304
It was Eun-joo?

00:02:22.559 --> 00:02:23.768
It was dear Eun-joo?

00:02:28.773 --> 00:02:29.899
How could that...

00:02:30.650 --> 00:02:32.277
But the real shocker

00:02:33.153 --> 00:02:35.154
Is that she knows more than anyone.

00:02:35.155 --> 00:02:37.490
The woman who we thought knew nothing!

00:02:38.408 --> 00:02:39.784
Why are you here?

00:02:42.745 --> 00:02:44.164
Did you follow me?

00:02:45.456 --> 00:02:47.792
No, I thought you were Se-yun.

00:02:50.628 --> 00:02:51.880
Why are <i>you</i> here, Mrs. Ahn?

00:02:53.339 --> 00:02:54.424
Se-yun?

00:02:56.676 --> 00:02:58.803
So you're the young man who went to the hotel?

00:02:59.470 --> 00:03:01.347
The one who asked if it was a murder?

00:03:05.602 --> 00:03:06.603
You

00:03:08.396 --> 00:03:09.564
Went to the hotel too?

00:03:17.030 --> 00:03:20.741
If you went to the hotel, you'll know. It was just an accident.

00:03:20.742 --> 00:03:23.828
And this is a family matter. It's none of your business!

00:03:24.329 --> 00:03:26.915
How can it be none of my business? A person died.

00:03:27.415 --> 00:03:29.667
You know it wasn't an accident, as the letter said.

00:03:34.130 --> 00:03:36.216
"I have the hospital CCTV footage."

00:03:38.885 --> 00:03:40.011
That letter.

00:03:42.096 --> 00:03:43.681
How much do you...

00:03:48.937 --> 00:03:50.230
What do you want?

00:03:50.897 --> 00:03:54.149
No, I don't want a thing. Don't worry.

00:03:54.150 --> 00:03:55.360
I just...

00:03:56.611 --> 00:03:59.072
I just want to know the truth. That's all.

00:04:01.157 --> 00:04:03.117
And I'm on <i>your</i> side.

00:04:04.369 --> 00:04:05.370
Not the police's.

00:04:08.373 --> 00:04:09.290
The police?

00:04:10.792 --> 00:04:13.044
If you won't tell me, I have no other choice.

00:04:14.545 --> 00:04:16.506
To uncover the truth about her death.

00:04:20.677 --> 00:04:21.970
<i>In the end,</i>

00:04:22.720 --> 00:04:24.389
<i>she told me everything.</i>

00:04:26.516 --> 00:04:29.643
Everything she said was so shocking. That's why I'm late.

00:04:29.644 --> 00:04:33.064
- I couldn't interrupt her. That's why I-- - Okay.

00:04:37.694 --> 00:04:38.861
I see.

00:04:39.487 --> 00:04:41.114
Okay. Calm down.

00:04:41.781 --> 00:04:44.325
Let's sit down first, and you can tell me.

00:04:48.746 --> 00:04:52.041
Now tell me everything you heard today.

00:04:52.875 --> 00:04:54.918
Don't leave anything out.

00:04:54.919 --> 00:04:56.004
All right.

00:04:56.963 --> 00:04:58.505
The story starts with--

00:04:58.506 --> 00:04:59.716
Wait, hold on.

00:05:23.531 --> 00:05:24.365
From now on...

00:05:26.326 --> 00:05:27.994
Talk quietly. Softly.

00:05:28.745 --> 00:05:29.829
Okay, so...

00:05:40.381 --> 00:05:41.382
Yes, hello?

00:05:46.804 --> 00:05:47.764
Really?

00:05:49.223 --> 00:05:50.224
Okay.

00:05:51.559 --> 00:05:52.477
Yes, I understand.

00:05:53.478 --> 00:05:54.520
I'll head there now.

00:05:55.021 --> 00:05:57.064
Hey, what are you doing?

00:05:57.065 --> 00:05:57.982
What is it?

00:05:59.400 --> 00:06:02.278
I'm sorry. I have something urgent to take care of.

00:06:03.613 --> 00:06:05.989
I'll call you later... no, tomorrow.

00:06:05.990 --> 00:06:07.699
Wait, tomorrow? Why?

00:06:07.700 --> 00:06:09.577
What is it?

00:06:10.161 --> 00:06:11.953
Did something happen to Eun-joo?

00:06:11.954 --> 00:06:13.455
Well? What is it?

00:06:13.456 --> 00:06:17.377
No, it doesn't concern Mrs. Ahn, but...

00:06:18.002 --> 00:06:20.128
Hey, you can't just leave like this!

00:06:20.129 --> 00:06:21.172
Wait.

00:06:22.256 --> 00:06:23.216
Lee Kang.

00:06:23.716 --> 00:06:24.634
Call me.

00:06:25.718 --> 00:06:27.345
Soon. Call as soon as you can!

00:06:36.604 --> 00:06:38.106
So when it comes to

00:06:39.399 --> 00:06:40.358
Literary incidents,

00:06:41.317 --> 00:06:43.736
It's not the incident itself that matters.

00:06:48.199 --> 00:06:50.535
Rather, the focus is on

00:06:51.869 --> 00:06:55.873
What kind of person gets caught up in said incident

00:06:56.374 --> 00:06:58.751
And what is revealed about their character.

00:07:04.173 --> 00:07:06.134
You little punk. Where are you?

00:07:10.263 --> 00:07:14.307
Why haven't you called? And why weren't you in...

00:07:14.308 --> 00:07:15.308
Hello.

00:07:15.309 --> 00:07:20.148
Why weren't you in class? Call me as soon as you hear this, okay?

00:07:22.233 --> 00:07:23.067
Hey, Kim Se-yun!

00:07:30.450 --> 00:07:31.284
Do you...

00:07:31.951 --> 00:07:32.910
Yes, Professor?

00:07:34.245 --> 00:07:35.121
Do you...

00:07:37.582 --> 00:07:38.916
Do you know where Lee...

00:07:45.131 --> 00:07:46.507
Never mind.

00:07:47.300 --> 00:07:48.134
You can go.

00:08:04.025 --> 00:08:06.569
If you have any ideas

00:08:07.403 --> 00:08:10.156
For new general education elective courses,

00:08:10.656 --> 00:08:12.617
Now's a great time to share them.

00:08:14.410 --> 00:08:17.329
The university administration has asked us to add

00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:19.624
More unique general education courses.

00:08:20.124 --> 00:08:21.125
Department Chair?

00:08:21.959 --> 00:08:23.711
LEE KANG

00:08:30.009 --> 00:08:31.009
Hey.

00:08:31.010 --> 00:08:34.263
<i>I'm sorry, Mr. Heo. I should have called sooner.</i>

00:08:34.847 --> 00:08:35.973
<i>Were you asleep?</i>

00:08:36.516 --> 00:08:37.850
No, go ahead.

00:08:39.101 --> 00:08:41.521
<i>Are you mad because I didn't answer your calls?</i>

00:08:42.021 --> 00:08:43.814
No, just talk.

00:08:44.357 --> 00:08:45.399
What happened?

00:08:48.194 --> 00:08:50.154
<i>It's a pretty long story.</i>

00:08:51.030 --> 00:08:52.198
<i>The call I got yesterday</i>

00:08:53.699 --> 00:08:55.284
<i>was from the nursing home.</i>

00:08:57.078 --> 00:09:00.456
You know about my dad being here from my assignment, right?

00:09:01.666 --> 00:09:04.001
Anyway, they called to say he'd gone missing,

00:09:04.669 --> 00:09:05.878
So I'm out of town.

00:09:08.297 --> 00:09:09.256
What, out of town?

00:09:09.257 --> 00:09:12.051
Yes, it's actually quite far.

00:09:22.228 --> 00:09:25.481
We found him, thankfully, so you don't have to worry, but

00:09:26.857 --> 00:09:29.777
<i>my dad's a little hurt.</i>

00:09:31.153 --> 00:09:32.862
<i>I'll have to stay here for a while.</i>

00:09:32.863 --> 00:09:34.699
Hey, then what about our conversation?

00:09:36.742 --> 00:09:37.577
Sorry?

00:09:39.829 --> 00:09:40.663
Right, yeah.

00:09:41.914 --> 00:09:45.167
How's your father? Is he doing okay?

00:09:45.668 --> 00:09:49.254
You mentioned that he struggles with alcoholism, didn't you?

00:09:49.255 --> 00:09:50.464
<i>Yes, that's right.</i>

00:09:51.424 --> 00:09:52.258
<i>You remember.</i>

00:09:52.883 --> 00:09:54.969
Of course I remember.

00:09:55.469 --> 00:09:57.179
I hope he gets better soon.

00:09:58.014 --> 00:09:58.931
But...

00:10:00.016 --> 00:10:03.394
Hey, what are we going to do about our conversation?

00:10:04.145 --> 00:10:07.690
Is it possible for you to write it up as your assignment?

00:10:11.485 --> 00:10:12.528
Assignment?

00:10:15.406 --> 00:10:18.159
I had to rush here, so I couldn't bring my laptop.

00:10:18.993 --> 00:10:21.703
Or we could do it over the phone. Let's do that.

00:10:21.704 --> 00:10:23.455
I'm free now. I have time.

00:10:23.456 --> 00:10:25.499
<i>No, I can't talk for long.</i>

00:10:30.379 --> 00:10:31.380
Okay, then.

00:10:32.048 --> 00:10:34.717
I'll try to borrow the computer at the nursing home office.

00:10:35.426 --> 00:10:38.136
I can't finish it in one go, but I'll try whenever I can.

00:10:38.137 --> 00:10:39.472
It might take about a week.

00:10:40.598 --> 00:10:41.931
What, a week?

00:10:41.932 --> 00:10:43.351
<i>Kang!</i>

00:10:43.851 --> 00:10:44.934
<i>I have to go.</i>

00:10:44.935 --> 00:10:47.312
<i>My dad keeps asking for me. I'll email you soon.</i>

00:10:47.313 --> 00:10:49.148
Hey, Lee Kang! Wait!

00:10:51.442 --> 00:10:52.610
You bastard!

00:10:56.280 --> 00:10:57.531
What? A week?

00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:02.119
A whole week?

00:11:14.215 --> 00:11:18.302
He said he'd email me soon. When exactly is "soon"?

00:11:19.387 --> 00:11:21.305
That little bastard.

00:11:27.269 --> 00:11:29.605
What the hell's with <i>this</i> bastard?

00:11:30.189 --> 00:11:33.108
Bastard drives like a goddamn maniac.

00:11:33.109 --> 00:11:34.401
Choi Dong-ju.

00:11:34.402 --> 00:11:35.319
Here.

00:11:38.406 --> 00:11:39.322
Choi Mi-gyeong.

00:11:39.323 --> 00:11:40.241
Here.

00:11:50.251 --> 00:11:53.087
<i>Mr. Heo. I just sent you my first assignment.</i>

00:11:53.671 --> 00:11:56.590
<i>I tried to write down what Mrs. Ahn told me, word for word.</i>

00:11:57.174 --> 00:11:58.300
<i>Brace yourself.</i>

00:12:04.223 --> 00:12:05.891
- Choi Bo-geom. - Here.

00:12:13.858 --> 00:12:14.775
Well...

00:12:16.360 --> 00:12:19.864
I'm sorry, but today's class is canceled.

00:12:20.906 --> 00:12:23.200
I'll make up for this class next time.

00:12:24.702 --> 00:12:25.577
Sorry?

00:12:25.578 --> 00:12:26.703
Class is...

00:12:26.704 --> 00:12:27.912
Canceled? Seriously?

00:12:27.913 --> 00:12:29.665
What's gotten into the old fart?

00:12:30.416 --> 00:12:32.209
Let's go to an Internet café and chill.

00:12:41.343 --> 00:12:42.552
Professor, hello.

00:12:42.553 --> 00:12:45.555
When can you send the exam questions for finals?

00:12:45.556 --> 00:12:46.474
Professor?

00:12:48.476 --> 00:12:49.310
What the heck?

00:12:49.894 --> 00:12:52.021
- Hello, sir. - What's up with him lately?

00:13:11.540 --> 00:13:15.252
<i>Actually, I've known for a long time</i>

00:13:15.961 --> 00:13:18.339
<i>that my husband was cheating on me.</i>

00:13:18.839 --> 00:13:20.216
<i>How could I not know?</i>

00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:23.719
But

00:13:24.929 --> 00:13:27.264
I've never brought it up and asked him.

00:13:27.765 --> 00:13:30.017
My pride wouldn't let me.

00:13:31.685 --> 00:13:33.103
I can't forgive him.

00:13:36.565 --> 00:13:39.318
But I thought I could play dumb

00:13:40.653 --> 00:13:42.321
To protect my children.

00:13:43.823 --> 00:13:45.241
So I just put up with it.

00:13:46.033 --> 00:13:47.326
Endured it.

00:13:50.454 --> 00:13:51.580
But

00:13:53.040 --> 00:13:55.584
I couldn't just let it slide this time.

00:13:58.420 --> 00:14:00.589
In my home, of all places.

00:14:05.094 --> 00:14:07.555
In our own home, where my babies live.

00:14:11.016 --> 00:14:13.769
With the likes of that worthless housekeeper.

00:15:45.069 --> 00:15:46.737
HAPPY TIME PREGNANCY TEST KIT

00:16:24.650 --> 00:16:25.609
What are you doing?

00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:30.781
What is this, Min-hui?

00:16:31.365 --> 00:16:32.783
What's this doing here?

00:16:34.493 --> 00:16:35.411
Why is that...

00:16:41.166 --> 00:16:42.876
How would I know?

00:17:01.270 --> 00:17:05.274
You're still awake. What's wrong? Should I turn off the lights?

00:17:06.692 --> 00:17:08.068
No, it's okay.

00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:13.991
What is it?

00:17:15.909 --> 00:17:17.619
Are you still upset over her?

00:17:18.120 --> 00:17:19.872
The fight you had earlier today?

00:17:20.998 --> 00:17:21.999
I don't know.

00:17:24.543 --> 00:17:26.336
It's bringing back memories.

00:17:27.337 --> 00:17:28.589
Min-hui

00:17:29.631 --> 00:17:31.675
Used to wear my clothes without asking.

00:17:32.885 --> 00:17:34.344
Bringing that up again?

00:17:34.845 --> 00:17:38.599
You were going to donate them anyway, so what's the big deal?

00:17:41.518 --> 00:17:42.936
Then what about the scarf?

00:17:44.104 --> 00:17:45.397
Why'd she steal what's mine?

00:17:46.065 --> 00:17:50.610
She said she never stole it when I followed her out and asked.

00:17:50.611 --> 00:17:52.571
Maybe you were mistaken.

00:17:53.197 --> 00:17:54.239
Mistaken?

00:17:56.283 --> 00:17:59.411
Are you taking her side right now?

00:18:00.120 --> 00:18:01.830
<i>I couldn't stand it.</i>

00:18:02.498 --> 00:18:04.958
<i>I had to put an end to it before Yun found out.</i>

00:18:22.226 --> 00:18:24.561
What brings you here, on a weekend,

00:18:26.313 --> 00:18:28.107
To a shabby neighborhood like this?

00:18:33.987 --> 00:18:35.906
Here to apologize or something?

00:18:41.745 --> 00:18:42.579
Why do you...

00:18:45.290 --> 00:18:47.501
I found it in your bag yesterday.

00:18:48.544 --> 00:18:50.712
I am aware of what this means.

00:18:52.631 --> 00:18:53.465
What it means?

00:18:56.760 --> 00:18:58.011
Seriously?

00:18:58.512 --> 00:19:00.055
So you think

00:19:01.014 --> 00:19:03.182
I'm pregnant with your husband's baby, lady?

00:19:03.183 --> 00:19:04.101
What?

00:19:04.852 --> 00:19:05.811
"Lady"?

00:19:06.728 --> 00:19:08.772
It looks like I'll be fired anyway.

00:19:09.523 --> 00:19:12.234
Are you saying I should call you "ma'am" even here?

00:19:14.903 --> 00:19:15.737
Fine.

00:19:17.865 --> 00:19:19.199
Call me whatever you want.

00:19:19.783 --> 00:19:20.909
But this...

00:19:24.538 --> 00:19:26.373
What is it that you want?

00:19:37.551 --> 00:19:38.927
Look, lady.

00:19:39.553 --> 00:19:41.847
No, you've got it all wrong.

00:19:42.806 --> 00:19:43.765
Ridiculous.

00:19:45.684 --> 00:19:46.810
You're crazy.

00:19:47.311 --> 00:19:48.854
Completely insane.

00:19:52.733 --> 00:19:53.817
Listen up,

00:19:54.401 --> 00:19:55.694
Lady.

00:19:57.863 --> 00:19:59.072
This

00:19:59.990 --> 00:20:02.910
Has nothing to do with your husband whatsoever.

00:20:04.077 --> 00:20:05.621
This is my private life.

00:20:07.080 --> 00:20:09.249
What do you take me for?

00:20:12.127 --> 00:20:13.253
Sure.

00:20:14.046 --> 00:20:17.299
It would be nice to snare a rich guy with something like this.

00:20:18.383 --> 00:20:20.177
But not your husband.

00:20:22.221 --> 00:20:25.432
Think I'm mad enough to mess around with a vile bastard like him?

00:20:26.016 --> 00:20:29.061
Think I'm like the bitches he fools around with behind your back?

00:20:30.687 --> 00:20:33.232
Who do you think he is? You really think he's all that?

00:20:34.858 --> 00:20:35.984
Don't be stupid.

00:20:37.277 --> 00:20:40.029
That husband of yours is just a revolting hypocrite,

00:20:40.030 --> 00:20:42.032
A thief who's fooling the world...

00:20:45.118 --> 00:20:47.704
And a fucking loser.

00:20:49.706 --> 00:20:51.291
You don't even know a thing.

00:20:52.751 --> 00:20:54.253
What? Thief?

00:20:55.587 --> 00:20:56.880
What do you mean...

00:21:05.514 --> 00:21:07.975
<i>What she told me was so shocking.</i>

00:21:08.517 --> 00:21:10.477
<i>A secret of my husband's</i>

00:21:11.061 --> 00:21:12.854
<i>that I could never have imagined.</i>

00:21:15.565 --> 00:21:16.650
TO BE CONTINUED...

00:21:18.819 --> 00:21:21.738
Continued. To be continued. It's always "to be continued.."!

00:21:23.615 --> 00:21:24.616
Unbelievable.

00:21:47.389 --> 00:21:48.307
Did you know...

00:21:52.060 --> 00:21:54.604
Hyeong-jong's book launch is the day after tomorrow?

00:21:55.188 --> 00:21:56.398
Seong-hui called.

00:21:56.898 --> 00:21:57.733
Yeah.

00:21:58.525 --> 00:22:01.737
I called Professor Park to say I can't make it. You can go by yourself.

00:22:03.447 --> 00:22:05.365
I hear Kim Su-hun will be there.

00:22:16.001 --> 00:22:19.046
And what exactly did Kim Su-hun steal?

00:22:19.546 --> 00:22:21.840
What theft did he commit, exactly?

00:22:26.720 --> 00:22:30.349
Yes, I know that you're busy and have your hands full.

00:22:30.849 --> 00:22:34.644
So just tell me that first. There's a reason I need to know now.

00:22:36.605 --> 00:22:37.522
Hey, Lee Kang.

00:22:38.231 --> 00:22:39.066
Lee Kang?

00:22:42.652 --> 00:22:44.738
That little shit.

00:23:00.504 --> 00:23:01.463
So,

00:23:02.798 --> 00:23:04.508
That theft he committed...

00:23:08.261 --> 00:23:09.596
There's no way.

00:23:14.976 --> 00:23:16.728
I have an older sister.

00:23:17.437 --> 00:23:18.688
I mean, "had."

00:23:19.940 --> 00:23:22.401
She was the only family member I was attached to,

00:23:23.860 --> 00:23:25.529
But she died of cancer last year.

00:23:28.949 --> 00:23:31.326
I only found out after her funeral

00:23:32.494 --> 00:23:33.745
That her dream...

00:23:36.123 --> 00:23:37.541
Was to become a writer.

00:23:46.049 --> 00:23:48.092
SHOULD I TELL MIN-HUI ABOUT MY DIAGNOSIS?

00:23:48.093 --> 00:23:50.220
THE DAY I FINISH THIS NOVEL, I'LL BE CURED

00:24:06.570 --> 00:24:09.281
GUESTS AFTER DARK SEON EUN-HUI

00:24:15.704 --> 00:24:17.247
Mom, what are you reading?

00:24:18.331 --> 00:24:19.166
What?

00:24:19.958 --> 00:24:22.627
Just something your aunt wrote.

00:24:24.337 --> 00:24:27.340
I always cursed her out for shutting herself up in her room.

00:24:27.841 --> 00:24:29.468
Guess she was writing this crap.

00:24:31.136 --> 00:24:32.721
Still, it must be good.

00:24:33.680 --> 00:24:35.765
I've never seen you read anything before.

00:24:38.643 --> 00:24:39.478
Sweetheart.

00:24:41.771 --> 00:24:44.691
Should I try to send this to a publisher?

00:24:45.192 --> 00:24:46.693
Publishers print books, right?

00:24:47.736 --> 00:24:48.570
Books?

00:24:49.404 --> 00:24:51.156
It might make us some money.

00:24:51.656 --> 00:24:54.326
Then I could pay for my smart girl's education

00:24:54.826 --> 00:24:56.036
And open a hair salon.

00:24:56.703 --> 00:24:58.121
Sure, try sending it.

00:24:58.914 --> 00:25:02.125
You said the man you work for makes a ton of money, too, right?

00:25:31.696 --> 00:25:34.157
Mr. Kim, sorry to interrupt.

00:25:35.158 --> 00:25:37.786
The manuscript I gave you last time.

00:25:38.286 --> 00:25:39.538
Did you read it?

00:25:40.455 --> 00:25:43.124
I've been waiting, but you haven't said anything about it.

00:25:44.167 --> 00:25:45.293
About what?

00:25:46.836 --> 00:25:49.880
You know, the thing I gave you last time. My sister's novel.

00:25:49.881 --> 00:25:51.758
I asked if you could read it.

00:25:56.930 --> 00:25:57.764
That.

00:25:58.932 --> 00:25:59.933
I'm sorry.

00:26:01.726 --> 00:26:03.478
My book's coming out soon,

00:26:04.145 --> 00:26:06.856
So I don't have time to read someone's rough draft.

00:26:10.860 --> 00:26:11.695
Okay.

00:26:12.195 --> 00:26:15.240
And you don't have to clean when I'm working.

00:26:16.366 --> 00:26:18.577
I thought I told you last time.

00:26:30.213 --> 00:26:32.424
Then could I have it back?

00:26:33.174 --> 00:26:35.218
I was going to send it to a publisher.

00:26:37.304 --> 00:26:38.513
Well,

00:26:39.222 --> 00:26:41.016
It should be around here somewhere.

00:26:41.516 --> 00:26:42.934
Where did I put it again?

00:26:44.352 --> 00:26:45.395
That's

00:26:46.396 --> 00:26:48.815
The only copy of the manuscript.

00:26:54.779 --> 00:26:56.072
All right.

00:26:56.865 --> 00:26:58.742
I'll find it and give it back to you.

00:27:08.710 --> 00:27:12.464
<i>I only found out after your husband's book was published.</i>

00:27:14.382 --> 00:27:15.216
Wait.

00:27:24.893 --> 00:27:26.978
What the fuck is this?

00:27:30.482 --> 00:27:31.524
EYES OF THE HOUSE

00:27:33.777 --> 00:27:36.112
I don't know what you're talking about.

00:27:37.489 --> 00:27:38.782
How are the two the same?

00:27:39.449 --> 00:27:41.034
Do you think I'm an idiot?

00:27:43.328 --> 00:27:45.121
A poor woman with no home...

00:27:46.247 --> 00:27:48.749
So, a woman who likes looking around people's homes

00:27:48.750 --> 00:27:51.585
Sneaks into a rich couple's house while they're on vacation

00:27:51.586 --> 00:27:53.672
And secretly stays there. That's the same.

00:27:54.673 --> 00:27:58.550
And here. The part where she finds a body in the fridge is also the same.

00:27:58.551 --> 00:27:59.719
Lady.

00:28:00.845 --> 00:28:01.888
Lady?

00:28:03.473 --> 00:28:05.600
Lady, what are you saying?

00:28:06.226 --> 00:28:08.353
Such a claim could get you in big trouble.

00:28:09.688 --> 00:28:11.314
What do you know about literature?

00:28:12.524 --> 00:28:14.651
Do you even know what a story is?

00:28:15.610 --> 00:28:18.279
If you keep making such baseless accusations,

00:28:18.780 --> 00:28:20.448
You'll have to face legal action.

00:28:23.076 --> 00:28:25.745
I don't fucking care. Cut the bullshit!

00:28:27.414 --> 00:28:29.540
You think I'll just let this slide?

00:28:29.541 --> 00:28:31.793
You really don't get it.

00:28:33.169 --> 00:28:35.547
Do you have any proof that I plagiarized her work?

00:28:36.548 --> 00:28:37.382
Proof?

00:28:37.882 --> 00:28:38.717
Yeah.

00:28:40.468 --> 00:28:43.388
Without proof, who do you think would believe you?

00:28:46.725 --> 00:28:47.684
I have it.

00:28:48.184 --> 00:28:49.144
Proof.

00:28:55.066 --> 00:28:56.526
My sister's novel.

00:28:59.279 --> 00:29:00.905
I have the original file.

00:29:09.080 --> 00:29:10.331
<i>From that day on,</i>

00:29:10.832 --> 00:29:13.501
<i>your husband was totally at my mercy.</i>

00:29:38.943 --> 00:29:42.197
<i>One word from me could ruin his whole life.</i>

00:29:42.739 --> 00:29:44.616
<i>A pathetic little fucker.</i>

00:29:48.453 --> 00:29:49.496
This is epic!

00:29:51.873 --> 00:29:55.460
Wow, is this honestly real? Is it?

00:29:57.170 --> 00:29:59.005
She called him a pathetic little fucker.

00:30:01.674 --> 00:30:05.094
He really is completely insane, isn't he?

00:30:06.221 --> 00:30:08.013
Mr. Kim Su-hun.

00:30:08.014 --> 00:30:10.141
Kim Su-hun. Hey, Su-hun!

00:30:10.642 --> 00:30:16.104
How could an esteemed author like you steal someone else's novel?

00:30:16.105 --> 00:30:18.774
You crazy son of a bitch, you fucking nutjob.

00:30:18.775 --> 00:30:21.945
So that's all you were, huh?

00:30:26.574 --> 00:30:28.368
All right, you son of a bitch.

00:30:29.244 --> 00:30:31.538
Let me see

00:30:32.288 --> 00:30:33.790
Just how shameless you are.

00:30:39.838 --> 00:30:43.591
Hey, it's me. I'm going. I'll attend the thing.

00:30:45.885 --> 00:30:47.344
What are you talking about?

00:30:47.345 --> 00:30:49.889
<i>I'll attend Professor Park's book launch.</i>

00:30:54.894 --> 00:30:56.104
Why all of a sudden?

00:30:59.065 --> 00:31:00.275
I guess you found out.

00:31:01.526 --> 00:31:05.237
Found out what? What are you talking about?

00:31:05.238 --> 00:31:08.449
<i>Kim Su-hun's wife. She's going to be there too.</i>

00:31:09.534 --> 00:31:11.286
<i>Isn't that what changed your mind?</i>

00:31:14.956 --> 00:31:17.166
Why didn't you tell me this earlier?

00:31:18.585 --> 00:31:20.169
I suggested that she be invited.

00:31:21.504 --> 00:31:22.755
You did? Why?

00:31:23.798 --> 00:31:26.133
I just wanted to see what kind of woman she is.

00:31:26.134 --> 00:31:29.053
<i>Why would you meet Eun-joo? What are you planning to do?</i>

00:31:31.389 --> 00:31:33.641
<i>She's going through a hard time right now.</i>

00:31:34.183 --> 00:31:36.227
<i>She has a lot on her mind.</i>

00:32:05.214 --> 00:32:07.091
<i>No, you're lying.</i>

00:32:08.426 --> 00:32:10.470
He'd never do something like that.

00:32:11.346 --> 00:32:13.640
Do you know how many books he's written?

00:32:14.390 --> 00:32:15.350
How could he...

00:32:17.393 --> 00:32:19.103
Steal someone's work like that?

00:32:20.396 --> 00:32:21.981
For fuck's sake.

00:32:23.399 --> 00:32:24.233
Look.

00:32:25.485 --> 00:32:28.237
Are you having trouble believing, or do you just not want to?

00:32:32.158 --> 00:32:32.992
See this?

00:32:34.994 --> 00:32:37.997
That bastard nearly killed me yesterday.

00:33:11.948 --> 00:33:13.116
Is that true?

00:33:14.283 --> 00:33:15.243
What?

00:33:17.203 --> 00:33:19.122
That you have the original file.

00:33:19.789 --> 00:33:24.877
Fucking hell. If you don't want to believe me, don't.

00:33:25.795 --> 00:33:27.714
I can just upload it online.

00:33:28.589 --> 00:33:30.174
Then give it to me.

00:33:30.675 --> 00:33:31.509
Sell it to me.

00:33:52.238 --> 00:33:53.364
Would this be enough?

00:34:13.384 --> 00:34:16.304
If I'd known this would happen, I'd have told you sooner.

00:34:18.222 --> 00:34:19.891
Now we're talking.

00:34:20.933 --> 00:34:22.185
That bastard

00:34:22.977 --> 00:34:24.312
Was way too stingy.

00:34:29.776 --> 00:34:31.652
Bring it to work with you on Monday.

00:34:33.863 --> 00:34:35.782
I'll have the money ready.

00:35:08.314 --> 00:35:09.941
Yes, hello?

00:35:10.900 --> 00:35:11.734
Excuse me?

00:35:12.443 --> 00:35:13.611
The police?

00:35:14.445 --> 00:35:16.697
<i>In the end, she never made it to work</i>

00:35:17.532 --> 00:35:19.367
<i>because she died on Sunday night.</i>

00:35:23.704 --> 00:35:24.997
<i>After that day...</i>

00:35:26.833 --> 00:35:28.584
<i>many things changed.</i>

00:35:32.797 --> 00:35:34.799
<i>Was it really a car accident?</i>

00:35:35.925 --> 00:35:36.801
<i>What if</i>

00:35:38.469 --> 00:35:40.012
<i>her death wasn't an accident?</i>

00:35:57.488 --> 00:35:59.574
<i>I couldn't just sit around.</i>

00:36:00.741 --> 00:36:03.119
<i>I had to find out the truth about her death.</i>

00:36:07.039 --> 00:36:07.874
A murder?

00:36:08.749 --> 00:36:10.960
<i>I was able to confirm that it was a car accident,</i>

00:36:11.544 --> 00:36:13.879
<i>but it did nothing to ease the burden.</i>

00:36:13.880 --> 00:36:16.174
No, don't ask the church volunteer group.

00:36:17.717 --> 00:36:19.634
No? Why not?

00:36:19.635 --> 00:36:21.637
Fundraising or whatever...

00:36:23.556 --> 00:36:24.931
Would take too long.

00:36:24.932 --> 00:36:27.351
The funeral should be held as soon as possible.

00:36:29.061 --> 00:36:31.814
People might talk.

00:36:32.607 --> 00:36:35.193
That would be disrespectful to the deceased.

00:36:36.235 --> 00:36:38.362
If money's the issue, we can take care of it.

00:36:39.238 --> 00:36:40.281
I'll pay for it.

00:36:43.117 --> 00:36:44.285
You will?

00:36:45.912 --> 00:36:48.414
- Just run. - What's your name? How old?

00:36:52.793 --> 00:36:54.502
<i>She's so mature for her age.</i>

00:36:54.503 --> 00:36:57.340
<i>It's almost concerning. She doesn't even cry.</i>

00:36:58.549 --> 00:37:00.718
What will happen to her now?

00:37:01.219 --> 00:37:04.888
Luckily, we were able to get in touch with her grandmother in the States.

00:37:04.889 --> 00:37:06.224
She leaves in two months.

00:37:08.184 --> 00:37:09.810
I'm relieved to hear

00:37:10.561 --> 00:37:12.271
She has family who'll take her in.

00:37:12.897 --> 00:37:16.024
I guess Eun-seo's mom had one last bit of luck.

00:37:16.025 --> 00:37:17.525
She was able to have a funeral,

00:37:17.526 --> 00:37:19.654
Albeit belatedly, thanks to a friend like you.

00:37:20.488 --> 00:37:23.491
How did you say you knew her again?

00:37:26.702 --> 00:37:27.703
If you could

00:37:28.621 --> 00:37:31.874
Use this money for the child's travel expenses to the States...

00:37:35.628 --> 00:37:37.880
I was indebted to her.

00:37:38.589 --> 00:37:39.882
This is only part of it.

00:37:42.802 --> 00:37:43.761
Director?

00:37:44.679 --> 00:37:45.554
Yes?

00:37:46.222 --> 00:37:47.723
I solved all the questions.

00:38:03.114 --> 00:38:05.408
The funeral is tomorrow.

00:38:06.534 --> 00:38:08.577
Did you pick your mom's memorial portrait?

00:38:39.150 --> 00:38:41.694
It's okay. Don't cry.

00:38:43.404 --> 00:38:44.488
It's okay.

00:39:00.671 --> 00:39:02.715
Hey, Eun-seo, your mom...

00:39:05.134 --> 00:39:06.969
Did your mom...

00:39:09.347 --> 00:39:13.351
Did she, by any chance,

00:39:14.352 --> 00:39:15.978
Have some sort of file?

00:39:17.605 --> 00:39:18.898
A USB?

00:39:33.371 --> 00:39:34.330
This?

00:39:38.125 --> 00:39:40.127
Mom said it was important

00:39:40.878 --> 00:39:42.922
And told me to keep it safe.

00:39:45.925 --> 00:39:47.593
The thing is, Eun-seo,

00:39:48.386 --> 00:39:49.804
This isn't actually

00:39:50.846 --> 00:39:51.680
Your mom's.

00:39:56.143 --> 00:39:57.520
It's mine.

00:40:11.951 --> 00:40:14.203
<i>I was just like him.</i>

00:40:15.329 --> 00:40:17.331
<i>No different from my husband.</i>

00:40:18.082 --> 00:40:20.876
<i>A disgusting, revolting person.</i>

00:40:38.602 --> 00:40:45.942
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

00:40:45.943 --> 00:40:50.155
<i>Happy birthday, dear Dad</i>

00:40:50.156 --> 00:40:52.115
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

00:40:52.116 --> 00:40:53.909
A WONDERFUL HUSBAND, DEPENDABLE DAD

00:41:04.086 --> 00:41:05.796
This is where it ends.

00:41:07.840 --> 00:41:09.383
It's all over now.

00:41:19.185 --> 00:41:21.394
Happy birthday, Dad!

00:41:21.395 --> 00:41:23.730
Thanks, everyone.

00:41:23.731 --> 00:41:25.440
Thank you, honey.

00:41:25.441 --> 00:41:26.734
My goodness.

00:41:32.781 --> 00:41:35.784
TO BE CONTINUED...

00:41:46.670 --> 00:41:50.257
How does this make any sense? How is this even possible?

00:41:52.343 --> 00:41:53.177
Look.

00:41:54.553 --> 00:41:58.432
She clearly knew what her husband did,

00:41:59.391 --> 00:42:02.978
So why would she get rid of the evidence and even let him hug her?

00:42:03.479 --> 00:42:06.773
<i>Why are you getting mad at me? I just wrote what I heard.</i>

00:42:06.774 --> 00:42:08.984
I'm not mad at you, you punk!

00:42:09.735 --> 00:42:13.822
It's just frustrating that she's covering for her scumbag husband, goddammit!

00:42:14.323 --> 00:42:15.282
<i>Mr. Heo.</i>

00:42:16.075 --> 00:42:17.659
<i>Are you jealous?</i>

00:42:17.660 --> 00:42:18.869
What? Jealous?

00:42:19.745 --> 00:42:22.331
You little punk. How dare you!

00:42:27.878 --> 00:42:29.505
Let's take my car today.

00:42:31.924 --> 00:42:33.425
That top is almost see-through.

00:42:34.677 --> 00:42:36.095
You really dolled yourself up.

00:42:37.096 --> 00:42:39.098
You're the one who dolled yourself up.

00:42:39.640 --> 00:42:42.226
I guess you wanted to look sharp for a certain someone.

00:42:53.195 --> 00:42:54.029
What's wrong?

00:42:55.197 --> 00:42:56.282
Stomach cramps.

00:42:57.449 --> 00:42:58.826
Since yesterday.

00:43:02.746 --> 00:43:03.998
Should I drive?

00:43:11.088 --> 00:43:12.047
Why don't you...

00:43:14.466 --> 00:43:15.676
Just stay home today?

00:43:18.846 --> 00:43:19.680
What?

00:43:22.057 --> 00:43:25.603
Stomach cramps are no joke. Go home and get some rest.

00:43:26.228 --> 00:43:27.896
I can go by myself.

00:43:30.608 --> 00:43:32.359
You don't want me to go, do you?

00:43:33.902 --> 00:43:34.987
Here you go again.

00:43:35.946 --> 00:43:39.325
I'm just worried about you, that's all.

00:43:39.867 --> 00:43:41.993
We're not getting any younger.

00:43:41.994 --> 00:43:45.623
We have to rest whenever we're sick. That's the only answer.

00:43:51.462 --> 00:43:52.713
Fine.

00:43:54.298 --> 00:43:55.215
Go by yourself.

00:44:00.721 --> 00:44:02.014
Go. Go on.

00:44:08.646 --> 00:44:10.980
I'll be back soon. Go in and rest up.

00:44:10.981 --> 00:44:14.610
And if it gets worse, go see a doctor.

00:44:49.186 --> 00:44:52.230
We'll now hear from Professor Park Hyeong-jong,

00:44:52.231 --> 00:44:54.691
The author of <i>Designing a Sustainable Future</i>.

00:44:54.692 --> 00:44:56.442
Let's invite him on stage.

00:44:56.443 --> 00:44:58.696
A big round of applause, please.

00:45:01.573 --> 00:45:03.909
Thank you.

00:45:06.704 --> 00:45:11.624
The host just gave such a wonderful introduction

00:45:11.625 --> 00:45:13.502
That I'm honestly overwhelmed.

00:45:14.294 --> 00:45:18.966
I didn't expect so many of you to come, but thanks to you, filling up the seats,

00:45:19.466 --> 00:45:22.845
I feel like I've become a best-selling author.

00:45:23.929 --> 00:45:25.430
Call me delusional, but hey.

00:45:25.431 --> 00:45:29.017
I'll work hard to become a best-selling author, maybe.

00:45:30.436 --> 00:45:31.978
- Right, so today... - You're here.

00:45:31.979 --> 00:45:34.397
I'd like to extend my heartfelt gratitude...

00:45:34.398 --> 00:45:35.857
Where's Hyeon-suk?

00:45:35.858 --> 00:45:39.527
...to you all for coming all this way to attend the launch of my book.

00:45:39.528 --> 00:45:42.655
- <i>Designing a Sustainable Future</i>. - They're not coming today.

00:45:42.656 --> 00:45:45.700
- Something urgent came up. - I'm truly humbled by your support.

00:45:45.701 --> 00:45:46.744
Thank you so much.

00:45:53.000 --> 00:45:54.668
Why didn't you tell me?

00:45:56.003 --> 00:45:58.714
You should have told me you were sick sooner.

00:46:00.340 --> 00:46:03.260
I didn't want you to worry.

00:46:05.095 --> 00:46:08.390
I'm okay now. Don't worry.

00:46:08.891 --> 00:46:13.437
Please, how can I not worry? Do you know how scared I was?

00:46:15.606 --> 00:46:19.151
Please don't get sick anymore, okay?

00:46:20.277 --> 00:46:21.695
Okay.

00:47:21.880 --> 00:47:23.674
<i>I thought everything would be over</i>

00:47:24.174 --> 00:47:26.218
<i>once I buried that secret.</i>

00:47:26.885 --> 00:47:28.136
<i>But it wasn't.</i>

00:47:29.721 --> 00:47:32.891
Yun, what are you doing? Come out here.

00:47:34.184 --> 00:47:35.644
Jeong-hu's leaving.

00:47:54.037 --> 00:47:55.664
What's wrong, Yun?

00:47:59.293 --> 00:48:00.919
Are you not feeling well?

00:48:04.548 --> 00:48:07.968
Are you still upset about what happened to Min-hui?

00:48:14.558 --> 00:48:16.518
How long are you going to keep this up?

00:48:17.352 --> 00:48:19.312
I have my limits too.

00:48:19.313 --> 00:48:21.564
Get up, Kim Se-yun.

00:48:21.565 --> 00:48:24.359
Now. Listen to your mother!

00:48:27.362 --> 00:48:28.988
They've already had her funeral.

00:48:28.989 --> 00:48:32.283
It's all over. When are you going to stop acting like a child?

00:48:32.284 --> 00:48:34.661
What do you mean, it's over?

00:48:36.580 --> 00:48:38.332
You have no idea, Mom.

00:48:41.251 --> 00:48:42.711
You don't know.

00:48:43.712 --> 00:48:45.630
You don't know anything.

00:48:45.631 --> 00:48:50.302
<i>That was when it all truly began.</i>

00:48:53.472 --> 00:48:54.806
Oh my God!

00:49:01.396 --> 00:49:02.397
You...

00:49:07.444 --> 00:49:08.737
You were there?

00:49:09.404 --> 00:49:10.530
I saw it.

00:49:12.491 --> 00:49:13.617
I saw everything.

00:49:14.993 --> 00:49:16.662
What Dad did.

00:49:17.913 --> 00:49:19.622
Look, she's bleeding! My God.

00:49:19.623 --> 00:49:20.916
Can you move?

00:49:24.211 --> 00:49:26.838
- She's alive. - She is.

00:49:30.342 --> 00:49:32.761
Please step aside.

00:49:43.397 --> 00:49:44.563
Please step aside.

00:49:44.564 --> 00:49:46.566
She's unconscious. Oh dear.

00:49:47.859 --> 00:49:48.985
Okay, let's lift her.

00:49:48.986 --> 00:49:50.654
Three, two, lift!

00:49:53.365 --> 00:49:55.116
Three, two, one.

00:49:55.117 --> 00:49:56.493
Let's move.

00:49:57.828 --> 00:49:58.745
<i>Min-hui</i>

00:49:59.329 --> 00:50:03.000
<i>was definitely conscious then.</i>

00:50:20.684 --> 00:50:22.644
Please keep tailing that car.

00:50:37.325 --> 00:50:39.202
Come on, sir.

00:50:53.133 --> 00:50:55.551
She was conscious when brought in. What happened?

00:50:55.552 --> 00:50:58.179
I'm not sure. I stepped out for a moment, and...

00:50:58.180 --> 00:51:00.182
- Get ready to perform CPR. - Will do.

00:51:08.065 --> 00:51:10.150
- Please page the clinical fellow. - Sure.

00:51:11.109 --> 00:51:12.943
No pulse. She's in cardiac arrest.

00:51:12.944 --> 00:51:14.653
Start compressions. Now.

00:51:14.654 --> 00:51:16.656
Starting compressions, now!

00:51:32.923 --> 00:51:34.674
- Epinephrine every three minutes. - Yes.

00:51:35.258 --> 00:51:37.844
- Intubate her as soon as we're ready. - Understood.

00:52:04.079 --> 00:52:04.996
So...

00:52:08.250 --> 00:52:10.127
So, your housekeeper...

00:52:11.628 --> 00:52:13.088
With your own two hands...

00:52:25.642 --> 00:52:27.018
No, Yun.

00:52:29.604 --> 00:52:31.022
Not yet.

00:52:33.108 --> 00:52:34.567
Nothing is certain.

00:52:34.568 --> 00:52:37.988
No, it was Dad's car. It was definitely Dad!

00:52:40.115 --> 00:52:42.242
Dad did something to her.

00:52:46.121 --> 00:52:47.122
My baby.

00:52:52.043 --> 00:52:53.753
I hoped you'd never find out.

00:53:02.637 --> 00:53:03.513
Mom.

00:53:05.265 --> 00:53:06.600
How did you...

00:53:10.187 --> 00:53:11.646
How long have you known?

00:53:15.483 --> 00:53:16.443
Yun.

00:53:17.903 --> 00:53:20.030
That's not important right now.

00:53:21.698 --> 00:53:24.075
Stop crying and listen to me.

00:53:25.118 --> 00:53:27.704
We now have to find out

00:53:28.330 --> 00:53:29.331
What Dad really did...

00:53:31.208 --> 00:53:33.001
For ourselves.

00:53:36.046 --> 00:53:37.172
How?

00:53:45.513 --> 00:53:49.768
How about we go see a late-night movie after this? It's been a while.

00:53:50.769 --> 00:53:51.895
A late-night movie?

00:53:53.313 --> 00:53:55.065
Or we could just go for a drive.

00:53:56.107 --> 00:53:57.399
Doesn't that sound wonderful?

00:53:57.400 --> 00:53:59.860
It'd be a waste to stay home on a night like this.

00:53:59.861 --> 00:54:03.615
No, I can't. I have plans, so I have to go out in a bit.

00:54:12.916 --> 00:54:16.252
You go to the hospital. I'll go to the park.

00:54:16.253 --> 00:54:18.088
When I meet your dad there,

00:54:18.838 --> 00:54:21.091
I'm going to question him about everything.

00:54:22.050 --> 00:54:26.471
In the meantime, you have to check the hospital's CCTV footage.

00:54:27.514 --> 00:54:28.515
Got it?

00:55:10.849 --> 00:55:13.268
Hey, Jeong-hu. Why are you calling me so late?

00:55:13.768 --> 00:55:14.728
What?

00:55:16.896 --> 00:55:19.274
Yun knows everything? What does he know?

00:55:22.902 --> 00:55:23.862
Jeong-hu.

00:55:24.571 --> 00:55:26.990
I have no idea what you're talking about.

00:55:27.574 --> 00:55:28.825
Let's meet up first.

00:55:29.868 --> 00:55:31.202
Let's talk in person.

00:55:57.354 --> 00:55:58.396
Hey, Yun.

00:55:59.356 --> 00:56:00.231
Did you find it?

00:56:00.732 --> 00:56:01.858
Did you check it?

00:56:14.871 --> 00:56:15.705
Se-yun.

00:56:21.878 --> 00:56:23.922
<i>Yun was crying.</i>

00:56:25.548 --> 00:56:27.550
He said the footage was useless.

00:56:30.261 --> 00:56:33.223
It was in a blind spot, so he couldn't see anything.

00:56:38.478 --> 00:56:40.855
It's over now. It's all over.

00:56:41.648 --> 00:56:45.568
We lost all the evidence we could've used to get a confession out of him.

00:56:48.780 --> 00:56:50.240
This is all my fault.

00:56:51.074 --> 00:56:53.284
I shouldn't have gotten rid of that file.

00:56:56.079 --> 00:56:58.706
I don't know how I'll face him from now on.

00:57:01.751 --> 00:57:03.545
It's so scary, so horrifying.

00:57:11.219 --> 00:57:12.887
I don't know what to do now.

00:57:16.182 --> 00:57:19.102
How am I meant to go on living?

00:57:28.361 --> 00:57:29.404
Eun-joo.

00:57:32.365 --> 00:57:33.241
It's okay.

00:57:37.078 --> 00:57:38.329
I'll help you.

00:57:40.248 --> 00:57:41.666
I'll do whatever it takes.

00:57:50.383 --> 00:57:51.634
Don't worry.

00:58:05.231 --> 00:58:10.361
MR. HEO MUN-OH

00:58:26.044 --> 00:58:26.878
Lee Kang.

00:58:28.213 --> 00:58:29.297
Listen carefully.

00:58:29.964 --> 00:58:31.174
That evidence.

00:58:32.217 --> 00:58:33.760
We can make it ourselves.

00:58:35.762 --> 00:58:36.929
What do you mean by--

00:58:36.930 --> 00:58:39.140
<i>Just listen to me, you punk!</i>

00:58:41.142 --> 00:58:44.395
That night, the night of Seon Min-hui's accident.

00:58:44.938 --> 00:58:47.440
You followed her to the hospital, okay?

00:58:48.024 --> 00:58:50.235
You followed Kim Su-hun to the hospital.

00:58:51.736 --> 00:58:52.569
What?

00:58:52.570 --> 00:58:53.905
And there,

00:58:54.948 --> 00:58:56.366
You witnessed it.

00:59:16.970 --> 00:59:19.514
You saw it with your own two eyes.

00:59:20.098 --> 00:59:21.349
Do you understand me?

00:59:22.350 --> 00:59:23.476
<i>Mr. Heo.</i>

00:59:24.561 --> 00:59:26.271
That will be how...

00:59:28.356 --> 00:59:29.983
Your story ends.

00:59:34.404 --> 00:59:37.407
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

01:02:03.511 --> 01:02:08.516
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

